</tr>
</table>
<p>Consider the 7-bit data word "0110101". To demonstrate how Hamming codes are calculated and used to detect an error, see the tables below. They use <b>d</b> to signify data bits and <b>p</b> to signify <a href="/wiki/Parity_bit" title="Parity bit">parity bits</a>.</p>
<p>Firstly the data bits are inserted into their appropriate positions and the parity bits calculated in each case using <i>even</i> parity. The diagram to the right shows which of the four parity bits cover which data bits.</p>
